race.comment: ZAIN PRINCE (5) returned to somewhere near his best last time when leading, only to be nabbed late. Backs up quickly and is drawn to advantage. Can go one better. SUPREME THUNDER (7) will get back again from the draw, but with genuine pace engaged he gets the chance to reel them in late. ROKABYE WARRIOR (4) disappointed at the midweeks when dropping out the back but backs up quickly and is worth forgiving. DON'T MATTA ME (15) was a sharp improver at Penhurst when closing off quickly from the back. Will drift back again but gets the tempo to launch late. Don't dismiss third up. SEE DE NIGHT (6) drove hard to arrive just in time at Mt Gambier. This is tougher but he deserves respect.
